1.Name: GPS Latitude Reference
1.Description: Indicates whether the latitude is North or South longitude; 'N' denotes North longitude, 'S' denotes South longitude

2.Name: GPS Latitude
2.Description: Indicates the latitude as three Rational values giving the degress, minutes and seconds respectively

3.Name: GPS Longitude Reference
3.Description: Indicates whether the longitude is East or West longitude; 'E' denotes East longitude, 'W' denotes West longitude

4.Name: GPS Longitude
4.Description: Indicates the longitude as three Rational values giving the degress, minutes and seconds respectively

5.Name: GPS Altitude Reference
5.Description: Indicates the altitude reference used for GPSAltitude; '0' denotes altitude above sea level, '1' denotes altitude below sea level

6.Name: GPS Altitude
6.Description: Indicates the altitude based on the reference in GPSAltitudeRef and expressed in meters

12.Name: GPS Speed Reference
12.Description: Indicates the unit used to express the GPS receiver speed of movement; 'K' denotes km/h, 'M' denotes miles per hour, 'N' denotes knots

13.Name: GPS Speed
13.Description: Indicates the speed of GPS receiver movement

16.Name: GPS Image Direction Reference
16.Description: Indicates the reference for giving the direction of the image when it is captured; 'T' denotes True Direction, 'M' denotes Magnetic Direction

17.Name: GPS Image Direction
17.Description: Indicates the direction of the image when it was captured

23.Name: GPS Destination Bearing Reference
23.Description: Indicates the reference used for giving the bearing to the destination point; 'T' denotes true direction and 'M' is magnetic direction

24.Name: GPS Destination Bearing
24.Description: Indicates the bearing to the destination point. The range of values is from 0.00 to 359.99

31.Name: GPS Horizontal Positioning Error
31.Description: Indicates horizontal positioning errors in meters
